race.comment: STREET ARTIST (4) is a speedy horse who has won his past two, dominant in fast time at Mornington two back before a solid win at Bendigo out to 1100m last time. He drops 2.5kg off that and coming back to 1000m looks more suitable. Tipping he can measure up. PALLATON (2) ran a much better race last time out in the Listed Brian Crowley, working home well behind the unbeaten and progressive Skyglider, who we'll get a good guide on through the Coolmore on Saturday. ALEPPO PINE (1) can be forgiven for last start in the Gothic Stakes behind Tentyris. He's not a 1200m horse, coming back in trip is far more suitable, albeit he's had a bit more exposure than some of these. CHOIR POINT (13) is off a smart maiden win at Pakenham that rated quite well, it wouldn't shock if she measured up, similarly VANGOGH BANKCHEQUE (10) who showed a nice turn of foot to win on debut at Echuca.
